  "deferred": [
    {
      "kind": "guardrails",
      "reason": "Screening-domain policies (no adverse-action notice before the pre-adverse response window has run; no report containing a hit whose identity match is below standard or whose record is 605(a)-obsolete; adjudication-matrix consistency and pattern-level adverse-rate disparity watch) require guardrail-service / OPA policy materialization, which Core does not expose as a pack surface yet. The behavioral core is partially covered today by Core invariants: every pack-configured agent is proposal-mode with four-eyes approval (agent-runtime), and the agent instructions + disposition taxonomy route final determinations exclusively to human adjudicators with the Screening Operations Manager as approver."
    },
    {
      "kind": "agent_recipes",
      "reason": "Bespoke LangGraph recipes (Hit Adjudication Copilot, Identity Resolution Assistant, Adverse Action Clock Sentinel, Individualized Assessment Builder) require agent-runtime graph-module registration (BRD 23 BR-12). This pack specializes the existing case-triage + analytics agents via TenantAgentConfig prompt_params + tenant-scope RAG grounding instead."
    },
    {
      "kind": "connection_templates",
      "reason": "Production read connectors (court-record aggregators and county/state repositories, DMV/MVR rails, education clearinghouses and registrar verification services, employment-verification bureaus, sanctions and registry lists, and the customer's ATS/HRIS for order intake) require customer credentials and pack-service connector materialization. The pack ships seed datasets in the exact landing shape; production connectors are configured through the product Data > Connections UI."
    },
    {
      "kind": "write_adapters",
      "reason": "Write adapters (send the pre-adverse-action packet \u2014 report copy + Summary of Rights \u2014 and the final adverse-action notice, publish the finished report to the employer's ATS, update the consumer file after a 611 reinvestigation, open a furnisher dispute) execute only behind pack-service's materialization contract and customer credentials; every such write stays proposal-mode with human approval \u2014 no autonomous notice, report release, or file change, ever."
    },
    {
      "kind": "eval_sets",
      "reason": "Golden eval sets (identity-match adjudication, 605(a) obsolescence screening, job-relatedness analysis, individualized-assessment assembly) require eval-service write APIs whose action names are not yet in the rbac canonical catalog (Core follow-up noted in rbac catalog.go)."
    },
    {
      "kind": "ontology",
      "reason": "Ontology registration (Applicant, ScreeningOrder, Package, ScreeningCheck, Hit, SourceRecord, Court, Employer, Position, AdverseActionNotice, ResponseWindow, Dispute, Reinvestigation) awaits pack-service; entity semantics are carried today by the screening_core semantic model and dataset schemas."
    },
    {
      "kind": "case_schemas",
      "reason": "Typed case schemas (hit_adjudication, identity_resolution, adverse_action_tracking, applicant_dispute, individualized_assessment) await case-service schema materialization; today's cases carry the same fields via display_projection + the disposition taxonomy."
    },
    {
      "kind": "model_archetypes",
      "reason": "Model archetypes (identity_match_confidence, hit_outcome_confidence) await experiment-service archetype APIs; the scoring capability ships as pipeline seeds instead (isolation_forest order anomaly + xgboost hit-outcome scorer) with model-governance expectations noted in grounding memories."
    },
    {
      "kind": "display_labels",
      "reason": "Display-label overlays (\"Screening hit\", \"Pre-adverse sent\", \"Response window closing\", \"Obsolete record\", entity templates) require the BFF label-registry endpoints (BFF-FR-082/088) which are pack-service-tier features."
    }
  ],
